President Obama met with supporters and volunteers of the Peace Corps on the 50th anniversary of President Kennedy's assassination. They paid tribute to Kennedy's legacy and discussed the importance of serving others at home and abroad. The President observed a moment of silence to honor Kennedy's memory. He also participated in a web-based videoconference with Peace Corps volunteers in Tanzania, learning about their work to promote food security, health, and youth empowerment in sub-Saharan Africa. Attendees at the meeting included the Acting Director of the Peace Corps, the CEO of the Special Olympics, a former Senator, and the President of the National Peace Corps Association, along with five Peace Corps volunteers serving in Tanzania.